<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-command"><strong>What Is Command Line Interface/CLI?</strong></h2>



<p>💡 The command line, or command-line interface (CLI), is a text-based interface that allows you to type commands via lines of text that are then processed by the computer.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="768" src="https://learntocodewith.me/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/command-line-1024x768.jpg" alt="command line screen" class="wp-image-21688" srcset="https://learntocodewith.me/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/command-line-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://learntocodewith.me/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/command-line-300x225.jpg 300w, https://learntocodewith.me/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/command-line-768x576.jpg 768w, https://learntocodewith.me/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/command-line-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://learntocodewith.me/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/command-line.jpg 1540w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>For example, you can learn how to use command line skills to quickly rename hundreds of files in a folder, completely erase a drive, navigate through files and folders, or pull up a list of every program installed on your computer — without ever using your mouse!</p>



<p>Depending on whether you use Windows or Mac/Linux, there will be differences in the CLI.</p>



<p>As Michael notes, &#8220;most distributions of Linux and Mac run bash as their choice of shell for the terminal.&#8221; Nonetheless, all of the commands are standard across Unix machines.</p>



<p>While Windows does have a command line interface, unless you work in IT or are doing <a href="https://learntocodewith.me/learn/penetration-testing/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">Penetration Testing</a>, Michael wouldn’t recommend learning it as a prerequisite. The Windows commands and how its CLI works are different from the Linux and Mac CLI.</p>


